5000|$|The design {{difference}} between the various models is the shape {{and size of the}} two compartments and in the way the <b>flush</b> <b>water</b> is introduced for the two compartments. In addition, the Roederig NoMix toilet was the only toilet that was able to collect the urine pure - without any <b>flush</b> <b>water</b> - due to a valve on the urine compartment that was opened when the user sat down and closed when the user stood up and flushed the toilet. It was also this valve that caused a lot of maintenance issues due to struvite precipitation in this valve. In the other urine diversion flush toilet models, the urine is diluted {{with a small amount of}} <b>flush</b> <b>water,</b> usually about one litre per flush.|$|E
